{"session_id":"svc-1778120265648198473","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-07T02:17:45.806745182Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable"},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-9f20a4bd-20260507T021742-0ff12c99","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260507T021742-0ff12c99/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260507T021742-0ff12c99/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260507T021742-0ff12c99/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260507T021742-0ff12c99/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260507T021742-0ff12c99/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Decomposition depth cap\u0026#xA;This bead is already at decomposition depth 2. Do not create another child layer; if it is still too large, reject the split with a short explanation and write no_changes_rationale.txt instead.\u0026#xA;\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-9f20a4bd\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eagent: move claim heartbeat out of beads.jsonl\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;`ddx work` currently refreshes claimed-bead liveness by rewriting `.ddx/beads.jsonl` every heartbeat interval. In this repo that dirties the git worktree continuously, creates tracker-only commit noise, increases merge conflict risk on the hottest tracker file, and mixes ephemeral worker liveness with durable bead state. FEAT-006 also states the worker/server boundary has no claim lease or heartbeat, so durable tracker heartbeats conflict with the intended execution contract.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:817-832 starts a heartbeat goroutine for each claimed candidate and calls `w.Store.Heartbeat(beadID)` on every ticker interval.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/bead/store.go:666-687 implements `Store.Heartbeat` by writing `execute-loop-heartbeat-at` and `updated_at` back into `.ddx/beads.jsonl`.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/config/types.go:160-164 and 198-206 expose a 30s default worker heartbeat interval, making the tracker rewrite periodic during normal operation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Stop writing periodic liveness heartbeats to `.ddx/beads.jsonl`. Durable tracker mutations should remain limited to semantic transitions such as claim, unclaim, close, cooldown, and append-only evidence/events.\u0026#xA;- Replace `Store.Heartbeat` usage in the work loop with an ephemeral liveness surface that does not dirty the tracker. Acceptable implementations include an ignored runtime lease file under `.ddx/workers/` or `.ddx/runs/`, server worker state, or another non-tracker runtime store.\u0026#xA;- Preserve stale-claim/watchdog behavior by teaching any stale-worker logic to read the new ephemeral liveness surface or, if no reliable runtime heartbeat exists, to rely only on explicit claim metadata plus process/server lifecycle cleanup.\u0026#xA;- Update C11/heartbeat extraction expectations if necessary so it extracts or removes the new safe liveness path rather than preserving tracker writes.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Changing bead claim semantics (`status=in_progress`, owner, claimed-at, claimed-pid).\u0026#xA;- Removing append-only execution evidence or semantic bead events.\u0026#xA;- Implementing the Axon bead backend; this bug applies to the JSONL tracker path.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DEPS\u0026#xA;- Depends on ddx-06eb05d8 because C7 is currently changing the same drain-loop area.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;INTERSECTIONS\u0026#xA;- ddx-0b8780db (C11 heartbeat extraction) should depend on this bead so the extraction does not preserve tracker-writing heartbeat behavior.\u0026#xA;- ddx-5cb6e6cd execution refactor should not close while periodic `.ddx/beads.jsonl` liveness writes remain in the work loop.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. `TestWorkLoop_ClaimLivenessDoesNotMutateBeadsJSONL` verifies a running claimed-bead liveness tick does not change `.ddx/beads.jsonl` bytes or the bead `updated_at` field.\u0026#xA;2. `TestWorkLoop_LivenessRecordedOutsideTracker` verifies the replacement liveness surface is written/read outside `.ddx/beads.jsonl` and is discoverable by worker/watchdog code.\u0026#xA;3. `TestStoreHeartbeat_RemovedOrNoTrackerWrite` verifies `Store.Heartbeat` is removed from the work-loop call path or becomes a non-mutating/deprecated no-op with no tracker write.\u0026#xA;4. WIRED-IN: `git grep \u0026#34;Store.Heartbeat|.Heartbeat(candidate.ID)|.Heartbeat(beadID)\u0026#34; cli/internal/agent cli/internal/server` shows no periodic worker liveness path writing through the bead JSONL store.\u0026#xA;5. C11 (`ddx-0b8780db`) either depends on this bead or its AC is updated to extract the safe liveness path, not the existing tracker-writing heartbeat.\u0026#xA;6. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/... ./internal/server/... -run \u0026#34;Heartbeat|Liveness|Watchdog|Claim\u0026#34; -count=1 passes.\u0026#xA;7. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/... ./internal/server/... passes.\u0026#xA;8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:agent, area:beads, kind:bug, reliability, refactor, spec:FEAT-006, spec:FEAT-010\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-5cb6e6cd\" spec-id=\"FEAT-006\" base-rev=\"d091a9e89ff4d1f7a867a513873f2af1ae9a0620\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260507T021742-0ff12c99\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-006\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-006-agent-service.md\"\u003eFeature: DDx Consumer of the Fizeau Execution Contract\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260507T021742-0ff12c99","base_rev":"d091a9e89ff4d1f7a867a513873f2af1ae9a0620","bead_id":"ddx-9f20a4bd","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260507T021742-0ff12c99","correlation_id":"ddx-9f20a4bd:20260507T021742-0ff12c99","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260507T021742-0ff12c99/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"c8234ee14defff7e84041102798a0300688e3999f42cd4d67d2e14cccfcd7999","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-f9d6cc6a","worker_id":""}}}
